OL,3,CMinisters consider law ensuring
OL,4,Cparents of critically ill children get
OL,5,Csupport
OL,7,F"No one should have to beg for time
OL,8,Foff when their child is fighting for
OL,9,Ftheir life," two parents have told ITV
OL,10,FNews in a plea to Keir Starmer to
OL,11,Fchange the law in the name of their
OL,12,Flate son.
OL,14,FCeri and Frances Menai-Davis are
OL,15,Fcampaigning for the government to
OL,16,Fbring in Hugh's Law, which would give
OL,17,Fparents statutory rights if their
OL,18,Fchild is critically ill.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/15
