OL,4,Cparents of critically ill children get
OL,5,Csupport
OL,7,FCeri and Frances say it means there is
OL,8,Fa "cruel gap in support", not based on
OL,9,Fthe severity of a child's illness but
OL,10,Fthe date they are diagnosed, leaving
OL,11,Fmany parents without income or job
OL,12,Fsecurity at the worst possible time.
OL,14,FHugh's Law "would offer families
OL,15,Fstability in their darkest hours, it's
OL,16,Fa moral obligation, not a luxury,"
OL,17,FCeri said, adding that parents are
OL,18,Foften forced to quit their jobs to
OL,19,Fstay by their poorly child's side.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
